    dc:description "Fig. 11. Coilodes punctipennis Arrow, 1909, ♂ at UCCC from Tropica Region Chapare, Bolivia (A, C–E), ♂ at CEMT from Cotococha, Napo, Ecuador (B), ♂ at DZUP from Tugurahua, Ecuador (F–G, J–K), and graphical representation (H–I). A. Body, dorsal view. B. Body, ventral view. C. Head, dorsal view. D. Head, ventral view. E. Pronotum, dorsal view. F–K. Male genitalia. F. Dorsal view. G. Ventral view. H. Right paramere. I. Left paramere. J. Right side. K. Left side. Scale bars: A–B = 1 mm; C–E = 0.5 mm; F–K = 0.2 mm." ;
